tip.text: Their specialty is schnitzel. If you enjoy large, tender, crisply breaded pieces of fried pork, you won't be disappointed. Service is fast & efficient too. Great for a quick lunch.
The warm, friendly staff were very welcoming (to both me & my dog) and the omelette was one of the best I have had in the city. Their selection of gourmet specialty foods is well-curated, too. A gem.

venue.name: Ahoy! Hot & Iced Chocolate, Lemonade, Waffle, Smoothie

tip.text: The filter-centric sibling to the My Little Melbourne family (they have siphon, aeropress, French press and other brew methods too). Nice bright space, the expected great coffee + friendly baristas.
The shio ramen is full of rich, meaty flavor...it's definitely one of the best bowls you'll find in the city. The rye noodles provide a great twist on a classic soup. Get it with egg!

venue.name: Higgs Field • Art Gallery and Cafe

tip.text: The tasting menu is full of hearty flavors, a nice mix of sea and land dishes. Desserts good too. Every plate was satisfying on its own terms. Service was friendly and managed a full house admirably.
Zona's a hip, classy gem on the Danube. Excellent food & wine overall. Service is attentive and swift. The amberjack with cold watermelon soup + artichoke was refreshing and unique, a must-try dish!
Although it's a fairly busy airport, this one is surprisingly calm. Nice spaces, clean, lots of places to eat. Grab yourself a Fazer chocolate at a shop and get acquainted with Moomin while you wait.
Two words: Porchetta Sandwich. If you're a fan of pork, do yourself a favor and try this tender little number. It's pretty much bursting with flavor. Make sure you have extra napkins nearby, though!
